1. License Rights
   1.1 You may copy, modify, create derivative works of, and run the Licensed Work for your internal business purposes.
   1.2 You may generate revenue using the Licensed Work on your own infrastructure (e.g., cost savings, internal services).
   1.3 You may not offer the Licensed Work or derivative works as a hosted service, SaaS, or commercial product.
   1.4 You may not sell, resell, rebrand, or redistribute official or modified binaries.
   1.5 You may not distribute derivative works or forks that compete with ESNODE or use the ESNODE marks without written permission from the Licensor.
   1.6 Only the Licensor may distribute official binaries or define commercial terms for ESNODE.

2. Source Availability
   2.1 The source code is available for review, learning, and internal use under this license.
   2.2 Any redistribution of source or binaries must retain this license text and may not circumvent the commercial restrictions in Section 1.

3. Trademarks
   3.1 “ESNODE”, ESNODE logos/icons, and “Estimatedstocks AB” are protected marks. Use is governed by /docs/TRADEMARK_POLICY.md.
   3.2 No trademark rights are granted by this license. Written permission is required for any use of the marks.

4. Contributions
   4.1 All contributors must agree to the Contributor License Agreement (/docs/CLA.md).
   4.2 Contributors retain copyright in their contributions but grant Licensor an exclusive, irrevocable, worldwide license to use, modify, sublicense, and relicense contributions under any terms.

5. Warranty Disclaimer
   THE LICENSED WORK IS PROVIDED “AS IS” AND “AS AVAILABLE”, WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. USE IS AT YOUR OWN RISK.

6. Limitation of Liability
   TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, LICENSOR IS NOT LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, SPECIAL, INCIDENTAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUE, DATA, OR GOODWILL.

7. Termination
   7.1 Any breach of this license (including commercial, distribution, or trademark violations) terminates your rights immediately.
   7.2 Upon termination, you must stop using and distributing the Licensed Work and destroy or return copies as instructed by Licensor.

8. Change License
   On the Change Date, this Licensed Work will be made available under the Apache License 2.0. Until then, the terms above apply.

9. Governing Law
   This license is governed by the laws of Sweden, without regard to conflict-of-law principles.

